cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the provision of services and applications to mobile users using airborne computing infrastructure, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of fog computing and mobile cloud in the clouds, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses system design issues that arise in the context of airborne computing infrastructure, which involves software engineering. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses issues of Big Data arising from such applications, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses interaction with users and drones using physical annotations, which involves the societal implications of technology.
